data.title: Yummy and cheap
data.text: It's a small place,  nice people, and most importantly, the food is great and cheap. Three adults meals with appetizer, sodas and tip all for fourty dollars.  Would go there again!

data.title: Great authentic Mexican food
data.text:
I come here all the time for lunch l. I love the tacos but everything I've tried is good. Nice staff and good music. Pro tip: go to the liquor store a block up from the store
and buy some coronas to enjoy with your meal.

data.title: Best authentic mexican in NJ hands down
data.text: Place is awesome. If you want the real deal mexican food this where its at. Everything homemade including killer salsa. They have rabbit, lengua, tripe soup all the goodies you will see at authentic joint. Mexico in jerzy!

data.title: Tacos tacos tacos
data.text: My husband and I visit this restaurant in a regular basis. Every time we go we order tacos and sometimes my husband orders sopes and can't complaint at all. Tacos are juicy and flavorful, freshly cook and sopes are big and home made as well as their sauces. Horchata it's great and also home made. The only con I find about this place is that it's pretty small so if you have a large group of people with you then definitely that's a problem. Prices are between cheap and reasonable. I would recommend this Mexican restaurant

data.title: La comida estaba regular
data.text: El lugar estaba muy pequeño y no es un ambiente agradable para estar con familia y amigos, ya que es muy sucio. Mala experiencia! Esperamos más de 20 minutos por 2 tacos
